First, we studied lithiated structures due to charging. Figure 2a,b, illustrates the Si-free and Si-doped iron oxide NPs, respectively, with Li atoms adsorbed on the surfaces. In this stage, the numbers of adsorbed Li atoms are the same between the two types of NPs. Poizot et al. demonstrated that the lithiation of transition-metal oxide NPs is accompanied by the nucleation of crystalline Li2O,1MxOy+2ye−+2yLi+→yLi2O+xM(M=Fe,Co,Ni,Cu),\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
