				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\,D={\min }_{b,A}\sqrt{\frac{1}{N}\sum _{i=1}^{N}{({{\bf{r}}}_{i}^{0}-{\bf{b}}-{\bf{A}}{{\bf{r}}}_{i}^{t})}^{2},}$$\end{document}where N, rti, b and A are the number of atoms in a NP, atomic position of the i-th atom at time t, translational vector and rotation matrix, respectively36. Figure 4b shows reduced D for the Si-doped system compared to that of the Si-free system, indicating that the structural stability of NP during delithiation is increased by Si-doping. In order to characterize topological stability, the Hamming distances DH of the NPs (Fig. 4c) were calculated to quantify the number of chemical bond-breakage and bond-formation events:3DH=12∑i,jN|δi,j0−δi,jt|,\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
