Structural stabilization and improvement of battery rate capability by Si-doping. (a–c) Time evolution of the average kinetic energy of dissociated Li atoms (a) geometrical deformation of NPs (b) and the Hamming distances (c) of the Si-free (black solid lines) and S-doped (red dashed lines) NPs during the delithiation simulations. (d) Experimental measurements of battery rate capabilities for the 2Fh (black), 20% Si-doped 2Fh (red) and their difference (blue with second y axis). In (a) cyan and yellow colors indicate the areas where the average kinetic energy for the Si-free system is greater and less than that for the Si-doped system, respectively.
